Great sentiments!!

--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, Frank Ratka &lt;warrior18eii@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; Everyone,
&gt; 
&gt; Can harmony and resonance be had? Yes it can. It takes a certain 
level of acceptance though. You have to accept the fact that every 
entity in existence is not spiritually equal but has the capability 
to become equal. Every entity has a right to this knowledge and has 
the ability to gain it with or without technical means. You have to 
accept that all realities are true in the eyes of those who behold 
them. Finally, you have to respect and accept people for what they 
are and know that all things will work out exactly how they are 
supposed to.
&gt; 
&gt; Regards,
&gt; Frank R.
&gt; 
&gt; ----- Original Message ----
&gt; From: Lisby &lt;lisby@...&gt;
&gt; To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
&gt; Sent: Thursday, November 29, 2007 10:54:03 AM
&gt; Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] chris(jack ass)moon at it again
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt;   
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt;     
&gt;             
&gt; I&#39;ll give him this: he has amazing balls to be using Frank&#39;s device 
and tell ing the rest who are also using them that his is the only 
one that works. If I were Frank, I&#39;d be beating my head against the 
wall. Oh. Wait. He already is.
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; What a total load of ego-driven crap. 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; Chris, if you&#39;re reading, may I suggest that you are the one who is 
falling victim to &quot;false&quot; communication? Or that your head is getting 
waaaay too big? Or if you already know that you&#39;re just in it for the 
cash, that you find another way to pay your bills?
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; You know, though, this same shit has happened to every group of 
paranormal researchers since the field began. I&#39;ve watched group 
after group come together and explode for thirty years because only 
the Chosen had the right to control the message, would broke no 
criticism of *any* of their own results *ever*, but had plenty of 
definitive pronouncements about everyone else&#39;s.
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; This is why I scoff at the idea of &quot;Harmony,&quot; with the capital H. I 
have seen the concept used by everyone from the Warrens in the 60s-
70s to the Harsch-Fischbachs in the early 80s to Moon today trying to 
use this idea of being somehow chosen and sacred in order to 
get &quot;real&quot; messages from spirit. Harmony is a way to control who gets 
to play and IMHO, it&#39;s a load of nonsense.
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; Bruce, I have to tell you that the message you got the other day 
about us being all Kumbaya set my alarms off, perhaps innocently, but 
nonetheless. I&#39;ve found there is such a fine line between real peace 
between brothers working for the real common good and peace between 
brothers as a mechanism of control. Yes, we need to be at peace to 
work together. But that peace has to be an inclusive peace. It has to 
be a peace within one&#39;s self above all else. It needs to be a 
*fearless* interior peace, too. The Harmony is within, folks. It&#39;s 
not judging whether others have it or not before we let them play. It 
is pure, unadulterated *internal* knowledge about one&#39;s self. Judge 
not, lest ye be judged--remember that one?
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; HMO YMMV, toujours,
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; Ann
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; On Nov 29, 2007, at 9:15 AM, bhali333 wrote:
&gt; 
&gt; Here is a blog steve sent me from moons myspace page as usual he&#39;s 
in 
&gt; a panic because his fraudulent buisness is going down the tubes. he 
